The paper deals with the problem of interval selection, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper proposes algorithms for estimating the cardinality of an optimal solution to the interval selection problem in the streaming model, where the input intervals are accessed sequentially and the memory is constrained. This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The paper also discusses the space complexity of the algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The paper uses probabilistic techniques to estimate the cardinality of the optimal solution, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also discusses the approximation algorithms for the interval selection problem, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds on the space complexity of the algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category.
